15/06/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The interior ministry issued a statement Saturday (14 June) in response to the US State Department's 2003 Trafficking in Persons Report.
The report concluded that Romania made significant progress in fighting human trafficking in 2002, and has become a leader in regional co-operation.
In its statement, the interior ministry said that co-operation with the United States on human trafficking prevention is a major priority.
(Rompres - 14/06/03)
